== Biography == In the 6th year of Empress Suiko's reign (598), she became a consort of Prince Shōtoku<ref name="denryaku"/>. She bore four sons and four daughters<ref>The ''Heishi Den Zakkanmon'' quoting the ''Jōgūki'' mentions three sons and four daughters.</ref>. One of her daughters, {{ill|Tsukishine no Himemiko|ja|舂米女王|12=draft}}, became a consort of her half-brother, {{ill|Yamashiro no Ōe no Ō|ja|山背大兄王|12=draft}}<ref name="teisetu"/>. She was trusted by Prince Shōtoku, who reportedly said, "We shall be buried together after death."<ref name="denryaku"/> In the 30th year of Empress Suiko's reign (622), she fell ill alongside Prince Shōtoku and passed away on the day before his death (February 21, old calendar). She was interred with him in the {{ill|Shinaga Ryo|ja|磯長陵|12=draft}} (current-day {{ill|Eifukuji|ja|叡福寺|12=draft}})<ref>Inscription on the halo of the {{ill|Shaka Triad|ja|釈迦三尊像|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Kondō (Hōryū-ji)|ja|法隆寺金堂|12=draft}}.</ref>.
