{{Citation needed|date=March 2021}} '''Kashiwade no Hokikimi no Iratsume''' (膳部菩岐々美郎女, ? - {{ill|February 21 (Lunisolar)|lt=February 21 (Lunisolar)|lt=February 21 (Japanese calendar)|ja|2月21日 (旧暦)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 21 (Japanese calendar)|qq=}} in the 30th year of [[:en:Empress Suiko|Empress Suiko]] (April 7, 622)) was a [[woman]] of the [[Asuka period]] and a consort of [[:en:Prince Shōtoku|Prince Shōtoku]]. She is also referred to as {{ill|Kashiwade no Ōomi (female)|ja|膳大娘|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashiwade no Ōomi (female)|qq=}}<ref name="denryaku">''{{ill|Shōtoku Taishi Denryaku|ja|聖徳太子伝暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōtoku Taishi Denryaku|qq=}}''</ref> and {{ill|Takahashi Hi|ja|高橋妃|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takahashi Hi|qq=}}<ref>Quoted from ''{{ill|Shitennōji Shōji Den|ja|四天王寺障子伝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitennōji Shōji Den|qq=}}'' in ''{{ill|Jōgū Taishi Shūiki|ja|上宮太子拾遺記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgū Taishi Shūiki|qq=}}''</ref>.
== Ancestry == She was a member of the {{ill|Kashiwade clan|ja|膳氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashiwade clan|qq=}}, a [[powerful clan]] active as {{ill|Tomobe|ja|伴造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobe|qq=}} in the 6th and 7th centuries. She was the daughter of {{ill|Kashiwade no Omi Katabuko|ja|膳傾子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kashiwade no Omi Katabuko|qq=}} (also known as Katabuko)<ref name="teisetu">''[[:en:Jōgū Shōtoku Hōō Teisetsu|Jōgū Shōtoku Hōō Teisetsu]]''</ref>. Her younger sister, Kashiwade no Hiriko no Iratsume, became the consort of Prince {{ill|Kume no Ōji|ja|来目皇子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kume no Ōji|qq=}}, a younger brother of Prince Shōtoku<ref>Quoted from ''{{ill|Jōgūki|ja|上宮記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgūki|qq=}}'' in ''{{ill|Jōgū Taishi Heishi Den Zakkanmon|ja|上宮太子平氏伝雑勘文|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōgū Taishi Heishi Den Zakkanmon|qq=}}''</ref>.
== Biography == In the 6th year of Empress Suiko's reign (598), she became a consort of Prince Shōtoku<ref name="denryaku"/>. She bore four sons and four daughters<ref>The ''Heishi Den Zakkanmon'' quoting the ''Jōgūki'' mentions three sons and four daughters.</ref>. One of her daughters, {{ill|Tsukishine no Himemiko|ja|舂米女王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukishine no Himemiko|qq=}}, became a consort of her half-brother, [[:en:Prince Yamashiro|Yamashiro no Ōe no Ō]]<ref name="teisetu"/>. She was trusted by Prince Shōtoku, who reportedly said, "We shall be buried together after death."<ref name="denryaku"/> In the 30th year of Empress Suiko's reign (622), she fell ill alongside Prince Shōtoku and passed away on the day before his death (February 21, old calendar). She was interred with him in the {{ill|Shinaga Ryo|ja|磯長陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinaga Ryo|qq=}} (current-day [[:en:Eifuku-ji|Eifukuji]])<ref>Inscription on the halo of the {{ill|Shaka Triad|ja|釈迦三尊像|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shaka Triad|qq=}} in the {{ill|Kondō (Hōryū-ji)|ja|法隆寺金堂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kondō (Hōryū-ji)|qq=}}.</ref>.
